Architecture plan for Issues #111-#112

Current structure:
- backend/src/routes/messages.rs owns message validation, client-key detection, in-memory rate limiting, database insert/list handlers, and message route unit tests.
- shared/src/messages.ts defines the cross-package message DTOs and Zod schemas consumed by the frontend and backend contract expectations.
- frontend/src/App.tsx contains MessageComposer, cooldown state, post-submit handling, and display of backend retry metadata.
- backend/tests/api.rs contains integration coverage for message posting, cooldown/rate-limit behavior, and end-to-end API flows.

Issue dependencies:
- #111 must be implemented first: replace the backend 30-second per-client cooldown with a sliding one-second frequency limiter that allows two posts per client key and rejects the third with 429 plus Retry-After/retry_after_ms metadata; reserved limiter entries must be released if DB insert fails.
- #112 depends on #111: preserve the client-side 30-second cooldown after successful posts, but treat the new backend 429 as a short frequency-limit warning rather than starting or extending the 30-second UI cooldown.

Key design decisions:
- Keep persistence in the existing PostgreSQL/sqlx message tables; no schema change is expected for a frequency limiter because it is transient request state.
- Model backend 429 response metadata explicitly in shared/src/messages.ts so frontend logic can distinguish server frequency limiting from successful local cooldown behavior.
- Update backend unit/integration tests around the new 2-msg/sec policy, Retry-After: 1 header, retry_after_ms payload, and DB-failure reservation release path.
- Update frontend tests/build expectations through existing TypeScript contracts; avoid changing unrelated TLHN layout, branding, routes, auth, storage, or database features.
